<main><article class="main-content"><p class="">We appreciate our involved parents and community members. We also enjoy broadcasting our latest news and information here on our News page, where we will chronicle school activities and student achievements and publish announcements. We’ll also offer helpful resources and information. So check back often; we’ll update it regularly.</p>
        
        <div class="pom-container">
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="update15covid19"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Update #15 COVID-19</div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class="">
<p class="">Update #15 COVID-19 School Closure: Extension of Distance Learning Format through June 12, 2020</p>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">Good Evening!</p>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">On April 1, 2020, the Los Angeles County Office of Education Superintendent, Debra Duardo, Ed.D., announced <a href="https://www.lacoe.edu/Home/News-Announcements/ID/4422/Los-Angeles-County-schools-chief-recommends-campus-closures-through-academic-year-due-to-COVID-19" title="" alt="" target="_blank" class="">she was recommending closure of all Los Angeles area school districts through the end of the 2019–2020 school year</a>. She has indicated that this is in support of the recommendations by the State Superintendent and the Governor's recommendations in order to maintain our safer at home order to flatten the curve of the predicted COVID-19 surge.</p>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">As a result of that recommendation and in consultation with the Santa Clarita Valley area school district superintendents, the Saugus Union School District will maintain its physical closure of school buildings while also maintaining its distance learning through the calendared end of the school year (June 12, 2020). School is still in session until June 12, and distance learning lessons and activities will continue to be provided, reviewed, and revised during this time.</p>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">I know this news brings with it many, many questions. Please understand that we are working through each of them now. In the coming days, we will be able to answer them, but right now, we wanted to provide confirmation of the information provided by today's governmental press conferences and announcements.</p>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">Please keep working with your child(ren)'s teacher(s) through Google Classroom and our distance learning protocols. While we know it is not the same as a traditional classroom setting, it is providing instruction for our students to progress. Now that this is our "new normal," we will continue to refine our practice to best address the needs of everyone involved. Please remember that April 6 through 10 is spring break and take the time to enjoy it. We will be back on April 13 with new lessons and activities for students.</p>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">Again, thank you to everyone involved in this absolutely unpredictable situation. The entire Saugus community has pulled together, and we all appreciate it immensely.</p>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">Take care, and stay tuned for more information.</p>
<div class="pom-container"><p class="">Colleen</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="Update11COVID19"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Update #11 COVID-19</div>
	<div class="newsbody">
<p class=""><strong>Update #11 COVID-19 and School Closure Extension</strong></p>
<p class="">Good Afternoon!</p>
<p class="">Many of you either saw or have heard of the press conference held by Governor Newsom and State Superintendent Thurmond on April 1. During that press conference and in a letter to county superintendents (sent March 31), Superintendent Thurmond indicated:</p>
<p class="">"Due to the current safety concerns and needs for ongoing social distancing, it currently appears that our students will not be able to return to school campuses before the end of the school year. This is in no way to suggest that school is over for the year, but rather we should put all efforts into strengthening our delivery of education through distance learning."</p>
<p class="">During this entire "safer at home" effort, we have taken direction on school closures from the Los Angeles County Office of Education (LACOE) and they have taken their direction from the California Department of Education (CDE). We are currently waiting for our direction from LACOE, before we can confirm that any SCV school districts will not have students return during the 2019–2020 school year.</p>
<p class="">We should have confirmation of LACOE direction on April 2, and we will provide the appropriate confirmation for our Saugus Union School District Community at that time. Until then, we continue with our distance learning implementation and following our "safer at home" orders.</p>
<p class="">Thank you for your patience and support during these truly uncertain times.</p>
<p class="">Colleen Hawkins, Ed.D</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="update10covid19andschoolclosureextension"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Update #10 COVID-19</div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class="">
<div class="pom-container"><p class=""><strong class="">Update #10 COVID-19 and School Closure Extension</strong></p></div>
<p class="">As of March 20, 2020, we were given direction from the California Department of Education (CDE) and the Los Angeles County Office of Education (LACOE) that the current school closures across Los Angeles County will be extended until Tuesday, May 5, 2020, (staff will return on May 4 to prepare).</p>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">While we know that this is an important step in flattening the curve in the spread of the virus, we also know that everyone is concerned about the prospect of continued learning for all of our students. I want to reassure everyone that SUSD is working to ensure that learning will be more than maintained during this extended closure. Our District Office team have been working during the week to prepare a distance learning protocol that will allow equity for students and will be able to be implemented by teachers and other service providers so all students can progress in their learning despite remaining "safer at home."</p>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">We anticipate being fully prepared to launch the enhanced distance learning format by March 30, 2020. During this weekend and early next week, families will receive more information on future schedules, availability of technology, platforms that will be used by the district, etc. Please check each Parent Square update to ensure you have all of the information needed to assist your child(ren) in being successful in their learning. We will also be communicating with staff during the weekend to ensure we prepare for future activities.</p>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">We know that many families have multiple children in multiple levels of school. We are examining best practices in homeschool instruction format to help us with time frames and allow us to make schedules enabling parents and students to access the important learning opportunities without competing interests for all children within a household. We hope to have some general schedules available by Wednesday, March 25.</p>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">We hope you will be patient with us and with yourselves during this time. Teaching is challenging. None of us have ever "done school" under these circumstances. Please know we are here to support you and your children. In SUSD, we believe that <strong>together</strong> we achieve more! <strong>Together</strong> we will accomplish learning during this health crisis.</p>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">Please continue to check Parent Square and social media updates for information on accessing internet services and meal provision for children under 18, etc.</p>
<div class="pom-container">
<p class="">Remember to continue social distancing and using preventative measures - wash your hands often.</p>
<div class="pom-container"><p class="">Take care and look for future updates,<br>Colleen</p></div>
</div>
